          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Bain’s takeover bid</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-dec-13-1.jpg" alt="Bain’s takeover bid" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Bain Capital is <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/investing/2024/12/12/bain-offers-to-buy-australias-insignia-in-17-billion-deal/" target="_blank">eyeing</a> Australia's Insignia Financial Ltd. with a $1.7 billion proposal. The private equity firm offered A$4 per share, marking a 30% premium on Insignia's stock price before the news broke. Insignia, managing A$319.6 billion in assets, is among several Australian wealth managers attracting global investors due to the country's booming pensions market. This deal follows other recent activity in Australia, including KKR's acquisition of Perpetual Ltd.'s wealth business.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
