          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Blackstone acquires Tokyo complex</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-dec-13-2.jpg" alt="Blackstone acquires Tokyo complex" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">
         Blackstone Inc. has <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/business/international/2024/12/12/blackstone-to-buy-tokyo-complex-from-seibu-for-26-billion/" target="_blank">struck</a> a record-breaking deal in Japan's real estate market, purchasing Tokyo Garden Terrace Kioicho for $2.6 billion. Located in Tokyo’s Chiyoda neighborhood features 1.2 million square feet of fully occupied offices, 135 residential units, a 250-key hotel, conference facilities, and retail space. Attracted by Japan's cheap yen and strong property performance, Blackstone plans to invest further in the property's refurbishment. Seibu, who developed the Tokyo Garden Terrace Kioicho will book ¥260.4 billion from the sale and will manage the property. Blackstone had its most active year in the country with transactions of $7.7 billion across its real estate and private equity business. 
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
